    "stark/proof/BatchOpening": {
      "title": "BatchOpening",
      "description": "Opened values for one committed matrix batch at a queried leaf index,\n together with the Merkle authentication proof.\n\n opened_values:\n   outer list — one entry per matrix committed in this batch.\n   inner list — base-field (Goldilocks) row values at the queried index.\n\n Goldilocks-specific sizes for the Fibonacci proof:\n   Trace batch  : 1 matrix, 2 columns → opened_values = [[left, right]]\n   Quotient batch: 2 chunk-domain matrices, 2 values each (DIMENSION = 2)\n                  → opened_values = [[qc0_c0, qc0_c1], [qc1_c0, qc1_c1]]\n\n opening_proof: Merkle siblings from the leaf to the root (ValMmcs::Proof).",
      "anyOf": [
        {
          "title": "BatchOpening",
          "dataType": "constructor",
          "index": 0,
          "fields": [
            {
              "title": "opened_values",
              "$ref": "#/definitions/List<List<Int>>"
            },
            {
              "title": "opening_proof",
              "$ref": "#/definitions/stark~1proof~1MerklePath"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "stark/proof/CommitPhaseStep<goldilocks/ext2/Ext2>": {
      "title": "CommitPhaseStep",
      "description": "One round in the FRI fold chain (CommitPhaseProofStep in Plonky3).\n\n log_arity      — log2 of the folding arity; always 1 in the current config\n                  (max_log_arity = 1 → binary folding per round).\n sibling_values — (arity - 1) = 1 extension-field sibling evaluations at\n                  the current domain index. Each is an Ext element.\n opening_proof  — Merkle siblings into the commit-phase codeword tree\n                  (ChallengeMmcs::Proof).",
      "anyOf": [
